<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,838,2017]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,946,972]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J" box="[485,696,947,973]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" refId="ref14730" refString="Grieshuber, J (2014) Guide to the butterflies of the Palearctic region. Pieridae Part II. Omnes Artes, Milano, 86 pp." type="book" year="2014">Grieshuber (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, this species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1889" box="[991,1087,947,973]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arida">
<emphasis box="[991,1087,947,973]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. arida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having: 1) male upper side ground color darker; 2) male upper side marginal band usually wider; 3) forewing underside dark submarginal spots more developed [this character is somewhat relevant to the dark suffusion on the wings upper side in female, as some dark females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1889" box="[400,494,1055,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arida">
<emphasis box="[400,494,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. arida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can have the large dark submarginal spots as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[1038,1181,1055,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[1038,1181,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]; 4) female upper side dark suffusion more developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,838,2017]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
In addition, the author found the following characters are also useful: 5) female hindwing underside ground color often uneven, not so uniform as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1889" box="[623,719,1163,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arida">
<emphasis box="[623,719,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. arida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 6) female hindwing underside pale submarginal spots usually paler and in greater contrast with the ground color than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1889" box="[804,897,1199,1225]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arida">
<emphasis box="[804,897,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. arida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,838,2017]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J" box="[355,564,1235,1261]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" refId="ref14730" refString="Grieshuber, J (2014) Guide to the butterflies of the Palearctic region. Pieridae Part II. Omnes Artes, Milano, 86 pp." type="book" year="2014">Grieshuber (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, this species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Grieshuber &amp; Churkin" authorityYear="2003" box="[855,964,1235,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wanda">
<emphasis box="[855,964,1235,1261]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. wanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having 1) size larger [specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Grieshuber &amp; Churkin" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wanda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. wanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Dulan area can be frequently as large as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[751,894,1271,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[751,894,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]; 2) male upper side ground color darker. In addition, the author found the following character is also useful: 3) female upper side black markings often darker and more in contrast with the pale ground color than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Grieshuber &amp; Churkin" authorityYear="2003" box="[727,834,1343,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wanda">
<emphasis box="[727,834,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. wanda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,838,2017]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,1378,1404]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Identification.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="adelaidae" authorityName="adelaidae Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[377,642,1379,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="adelaidae" subSpecies="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[377,642,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been known only from Xiahe, the 
<typeStatus box="[1095,1143,1379,1405]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">type</typeStatus>
locality. Specimens from Dulan area are identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="adelaidae" authorityName="adelaidae Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[466,726,1415,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="adelaidae" subSpecies="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[466,726,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because they fit 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J" box="[922,1148,1415,1441]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" refId="ref14730" refString="Grieshuber, J (2014) Guide to the butterflies of the Palearctic region. Pieridae Part II. Omnes Artes, Milano, 86 pp." type="book" year="2014">Grieshuber’s (2014)</bibRefCitation>
diagnostic description on good number of the topotypic specimens. One of the female specimens from Dulan area (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1257,1451,1477]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[217,1370,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Habitus of Colias taxa ♂♂ &amp; ♀♀ at same scale (Upper half- upper side; lower half- underside). 1—Colias adelaidae adelaidae; 2—Colias arida cakana; 3—Colias wanda wanda. Serial number unique for each specimen. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6333775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6333775/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 1- A2</figureCitation>
) looks very like a female in G.C. Bozano’s collection, figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J" box="[701,943,1486,1513]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" refId="ref14730" refString="Grieshuber, J (2014) Guide to the butterflies of the Palearctic region. Pieridae Part II. Omnes Artes, Milano, 86 pp." type="book" year="2014">Grieshuber (2014: 59</bibRefCitation>
, figs. for left 
<specimenCount box="[1095,1114,1487,1513]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
), except for the shape of the wings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,838,2017]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1559,1585]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Taxonomy</emphasis>
. There were arguments on the status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[772,914,1559,1585]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[772,914,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in literature: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rose, K. &amp; Schulte, A." box="[1066,1324,1559,1585]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="93 - 104" refId="ref16020" refString="Rose, K. &amp; Schulte, A. (1992) Ein Beitrag zur systematischen Stellung und subspezifischen Gliederung von Colias arida Alpheraky 1889. Nachrichten des entomologischen Vereins Apollo, Neue Folge, 13 (2), 93 - 104, pls. 1 - 2. [in Germany]" type="journal article" year="1992">Rose &amp; Schulte (1992)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelaidae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1889" box="[482,577,1595,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arida">
<emphasis box="[482,577,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. arida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whilst Verhulst (1991, 2000), 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoshiai, A." box="[931,1101,1595,1622]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="8 - 10" refId="ref15351" refString="Hoshiai, A. (1996) Notes of Colias from China and surrounding area (1). In: Koiwaya, S. (Ed.), Studies of Chinese Butterflies. Vol. 3. S. Koiwaya, Tokyo, pp. 211 - 217, pls. 8 - 10. [in Japanese]" type="book chapter" year="1996">Hoshiai (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J." box="[1158,1358,1595,1621]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="41 - 48" refId="ref14631" refString="Grieshuber, J. (1999) Zur Artengruppe Colias arida Alpheraky, 1889, adelaidae Verhulst, 1991, baeckeri Kotzsch, 1930 und stoliczkana Moore, 1878. Beschreibung einer neuen Unterart von Colias adelaidae (Lepidoptera: Pieridae). Lambillionea, 99 (1), 41 - 48. [in Germany]" type="journal article" year="1999">Grieshuber (1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J" box="[1371,1429,1595,1621]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" refId="ref14730" refString="Grieshuber, J (2014) Guide to the butterflies of the Palearctic region. Pieridae Part II. Omnes Artes, Milano, 86 pp." type="book" year="2014">2014</bibRefCitation>
) treated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[235,378,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[235,378,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct species. However, the discovery of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[909,1052,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[909,1052,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Dulan, an area close to Wulan-Tianjun area where 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rose &amp; Schulte" authorityYear="1992" box="[418,601,1667,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arida" subSpecies="cakana">
<emphasis box="[418,601,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. arida cakana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flies, gives a clue for this taxonomic problem. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="adelaidae" authorityName="adelaidae Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="adelaidae" subSpecies="adelaidae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Dulan area are in common with those from Xiahe, not showing any transitional characters to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rose &amp; Schulte" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arida" subSpecies="cakana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. arida cakana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Such distributional patterns of 
<taxonomicName authority="adelaidae" authorityName="adelaidae Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[658,918,1739,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="adelaidae" subSpecies="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[658,918,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rose &amp; Schulte" authorityYear="1992" box="[972,1153,1739,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arida" subSpecies="cakana">
<emphasis box="[972,1153,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. arida cakana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggest that the two taxa are specifically distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,838,2017]" box="[199,580,1810,1837]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,356,1810,1836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Flight period</emphasis>
. Mid July at Dulan.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,838,2017]" box="[199,499,1846,1873]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,1846,1872]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Altitude</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[311,389,1847,1873]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" unit="m" value="3700.0">3700m</quantity>
at Dulan.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,838,2017]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,1882,1909]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Distributional notes.</emphasis>
This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhulst" authorityYear="1991" box="[756,901,1883,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelaidae">
<emphasis box="[756,901,1883,1909]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Central 
<collectingRegion box="[1067,1161,1883,1909]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
. Another subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="Grieshuber, 1999" authorityName="Grieshuber" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Pieridae" genus="Colias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="adelaidae" subSpecies="karmalana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">C. adelaidae karmalana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grieshuber, J." box="[397,590,1919,1945]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="41 - 48" refId="ref14631" refString="Grieshuber, J. (1999) Zur Artengruppe Colias arida Alpheraky, 1889, adelaidae Verhulst, 1991, baeckeri Kotzsch, 1930 und stoliczkana Moore, 1878. Beschreibung einer neuen Unterart von Colias adelaidae (Lepidoptera: Pieridae). Lambillionea, 99 (1), 41 - 48. [in Germany]" type="journal article" year="1999">Grieshuber, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is known from eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[854,912,1919,1945]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Tibet</collectingRegion>
(Karma La = Yela, S. of Bangda; Dahmo La = Dama La, E. of Qamdo). It is heard that this species is also collected by some people from Chengduo, Yushu, SE. 
<collectingRegion box="[151,241,1991,2017]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
and Shiqu, NW. 
<collectingRegion box="[433,526,1991,2017]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, but further information is unknown (Y. Yang, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
